{"repo": "coreruleset/coreruleset", "pull_number": 4182, "instance_id": "coreruleset__coreruleset-4182", "issue_numbers": [4174], "base_commit": "a35c12b6720ccb27c3fb987c209b7df5daba2bb8", "patch": "diff --git a/.github/workflows/lint.yaml b/.github/workflows/lint.yaml\nindex f72008ebf6..fa3ce6e258 100644\n--- a/.github/workflows/lint.yaml\n+++ b/.github/workflows/lint.yaml\n@@ -41,7 +41,6 @@ jobs:\n         with:\n           python-version: 3.x\n \n-      - uses: pre-commit/action@2c7b3805fd2a0fd8c1884dcaebf91fc102a13ecd # v3.0.1\n \n       - name: \"Check CRS syntax\"\n         run: |\ndiff --git a/.pre-commit-config.yaml b/.pre-commit-config.yaml\nindex 4e7a124021..9763a924ff 100644\n--- a/.pre-commit-config.yaml\n+++ b/.pre-commit-config.yaml\n@@ -1,4 +1,12 @@\n ---\n+ci:\n+    autofix_commit_msg: |\n+        chore(formatting): auto fixes from pre-commit hooks\n+\n+        for more information, see https://pre-commit.ci\n+    autofix_prs: true\n+    skip: []\n+    submodules: false\n # Update the rev variable with the release version that you want, from the yamllint repo\n # You can pass your custom .yamllint with args attribute.\n repos:\n@@ -11,3 +19,17 @@ repos:\n     - id: trailing-whitespace\n       exclude: '^regex-assembly/'\n       args: [--markdown-linebreak-ext=md]\n+- repo: https://github.com/adrienverge/yamllint.git\n+  rev: v1.29.0\n+  hooks:\n+    - id: yamllint\n+      args: [-f=github, -c=.yamllint.yml, tests/regression/tests]\n+- repo: local\n+  hooks:\n+    - id: run-crs-toolchain\n+      name: run-crs-toolchain\n+      entry: crs-toolchain regex update --all -l error\n+      additional_dependencies: ['github.com/coreruleset/crs-toolchain/v2@v2.4.0']\n+      language: golang\n+      pass_filenames: false\n+      files: '^regex-assembly/'\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add pre-commit to execute crs-toolchain to fix when regexes are changed\n### Description\n\nIt is getting annoying to run crs-toolchain whenever we accept a code review in any regex, as the rule will be outdated and CI will fail.\n\nLet's run pre-commit and update automatically whenever regex files change and run the update. If there are changes, we commit to the branch and then there is no need for doing it manually.\n\n### Confirmation\n\n- [x] I have removed any personal data (email addresses, IP addresses, passwords, domain names) from any logs posted.\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/6845928ae76f876fa2c4bd2f868b973040dabbe5", "https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/81421760071f7641f5b721dbeeed2c5189a09047", "https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/dabafc9268beec7c08db552b1d0d3d18d8b21ab9", "https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/77e79cc782ef5e39b7e7b3de3eee3019bf483e52", "https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/a09ffd39efe3f0d10aa7a84a143dd55c039b8abe", "https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/3cd2b23d6f39396ff249249a15cbc022023e7b7c", "https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/9a986c4f1933b83942bc1e65bb227e03a958e405", "https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/406598a25600a872672389261ea9c630be38218e", "https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/63ef70414d14b5001d0f4c5d51cf45f2d539bd9a", "https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/a8478815c4d53731daa895fc931c4f0cdb272146", "https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/c02ea6f287fc375d5c1aedcb13aef82fdc26ede0"], "created_at": "2025-07-07T11:20:36Z"}
{"repo": "coreruleset/coreruleset", "pull_number": 4193, "instance_id": "coreruleset__coreruleset-4193", "issue_numbers": [4192], "base_commit": "a35c12b6720ccb27c3fb987c209b7df5daba2bb8", "patch": "diff --git a/regex-assembly/931130.ra b/regex-assembly/931130.ra\nindex 558f5da468..7bf37d2988 100644\n--- a/regex-assembly/931130.ra\n+++ b/regex-assembly/931130.ra\n@@ -12,6 +12,6 @@\n   ##!=>\n   ##!> include url-schemes\n   ##!=>\n-  ://(?:[^@]+@)?([^/]*)\n+  ://?(?:[^@]+@)?([^/]*)\n   ##!=>\n ##!<\ndiff --git a/rules/REQUEST-931-APPLICATION-ATTACK-RFI.conf b/rules/REQUEST-931-APPLICATION-ATTACK-RFI.conf\nindex d3a8e07add..13cc51eea1 100644\n--- a/rules/REQUEST-931-APPLICATION-ATTACK-RFI.conf\n+++ b/rules/REQUEST-931-APPLICATION-ATTACK-RFI.conf\n@@ -116,7 +116,7 @@ SecRule TX:DETECTION_PARANOIA_LEVEL \"@lt 2\" \"id:931014,phase:2,pass,nolog,tag:'O\n # (consult https://coreruleset.org/docs/development/regex_assembly/ for details):\n #   crs-toolchain regex update 931130\n #\n-SecRule ARGS \"@rx (?i)(?:(?:url|jar):)?(?:a(?:cap|f[ps]|ttachment)|b(?:eshare|itcoin|lob)|c(?:a(?:llto|p)|id|vs|ompress.(?:zlib|bzip2))|d(?:a(?:v|ta)|ict|n(?:s|tp))|e(?:d2k|xpect)|f(?:(?:ee)?d|i(?:le|nger|sh)|tps?)|g(?:it|o(?:pher)?|lob)|h(?:323|ttps?)|i(?:ax|cap|(?:ma|p)ps?|rc[6s]?)|ja(?:bbe)?r|l(?:dap[is]?|ocal_file)|m(?:a(?:ilto|ven)|ms|umble)|n(?:e(?:tdoc|ws)|fs|ntps?)|ogg|p(?:aparazzi|h(?:ar|p)|op(?:2|3s?)|r(?:es|oxy)|syc)|r(?:mi|sync|tm(?:f?p)?|ar)|s(?:3|ftp|ips?|m(?:[bs]|tps?)|n(?:ews|mp)|sh(?:2(?:.(?:s(?:hell|(?:ft|c)p)|exec|tunnel))?)?|vn(?:\\+ssh)?)|t(?:e(?:amspeak|lnet)|ftp|urns?)|u(?:dp|nreal|t2004)|v(?:entrilo|iew-source|nc)|w(?:ebcal|ss?)|x(?:mpp|ri)|zip)://(?:[^@]+@)?([^/]*)\" \\\n+SecRule ARGS \"@rx (?i)(?:(?:url|jar):)?(?:a(?:cap|f[ps]|ttachment)|b(?:eshare|itcoin|lob)|c(?:a(?:llto|p)|id|vs|ompress.(?:zlib|bzip2))|d(?:a(?:v|ta)|ict|n(?:s|tp))|e(?:d2k|xpect)|f(?:(?:ee)?d|i(?:le|nger|sh)|tps?)|g(?:it|o(?:pher)?|lob)|h(?:323|ttps?)|i(?:ax|cap|(?:ma|p)ps?|rc[6s]?)|ja(?:bbe)?r|l(?:dap[is]?|ocal_file)|m(?:a(?:ilto|ven)|ms|umble)|n(?:e(?:tdoc|ws)|fs|ntps?)|ogg|p(?:aparazzi|h(?:ar|p)|op(?:2|3s?)|r(?:es|oxy)|syc)|r(?:mi|sync|tm(?:f?p)?|ar)|s(?:3|ftp|ips?|m(?:[bs]|tps?)|n(?:ews|mp)|sh(?:2(?:.(?:s(?:hell|(?:ft|c)p)|exec|tunnel))?)?|vn(?:\\+ssh)?)|t(?:e(?:amspeak|lnet)|ftp|urns?)|u(?:dp|nreal|t2004)|v(?:entrilo|iew-source|nc)|w(?:ebcal|ss?)|x(?:mpp|ri)|zip)://?(?:[^@]+@)?([^/]*)\" \\\n     \"id:931130,\\\n     phase:2,\\\n     block,\\\n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/tests/regression/tests/REQUEST-931-APPLICATION-ATTACK-RFI/931130.yaml b/tests/regression/tests/REQUEST-931-APPLICATION-ATTACK-RFI/931130.yaml\nindex d67a67c032..65a7010ccd 100644\n--- a/tests/regression/tests/REQUEST-931-APPLICATION-ATTACK-RFI/931130.yaml\n+++ b/tests/regression/tests/REQUEST-931-APPLICATION-ATTACK-RFI/931130.yaml\n@@ -355,3 +355,19 @@ tests:\n         output:\n           log:\n             expect_ids: [931130]\n+  - test_id: 23\n+    desc: Remote File Inclusion Attack (931130) with Java backend using file:/\n+    stages:\n+      - input:\n+          dest_addr: 127.0.0.1\n+          headers:\n+            User-Agent: \"OWASP CRS test agent\"\n+            Host: localhost\n+            Accept: text/xml,application/xml,application/xhtml+xml,text/html;q=0.9,text/plain;q=0.8,image/png,*/*;q=0.5\n+          method: GET\n+          port: 80\n+          uri: \"/get?x=jar:file:/path/to/myApp.jar!/com/example/data.txt\"\n+          version: HTTP/1.1\n+        output:\n+          log:\n+            expect_ids: [931130]\n", "problem_statement": "WAF Bypass via jar:file uri schema\nHi team,\n\nWhile testing the Coraza WAF sandbox, I noticed that the following payload passes without detection or blocking\n```bash\ncurl -ig -H \"x-format-output: txt-matched-rules\" -H \"x-crs-paranoia-level: 3\" -H \"x-backend: coraza-caddy\" --data-urlencode \"q=jar:file:/path/to/myApp.jar\\!/com/example/data.txt\" \"https://sandbox.coreruleset.org/\"\n```\nresult is\n```\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\nDate: Wed, 09 Jul 2025 14:28:25 GMT\nContent-Type: text/plain\nTransfer-Encoding: chunked\nConnection: keep-alive\nX-Unique-ID: aG58idhepdrEuls4eH65lwAAAEg\nx-backend: invalid, fallback to apache-latest\nx-crs-last-commit: none\n```\n- The WAF should detect or block this unusual URI scheme input to prevent potential exploitation.\n\n\nimpact of this *If a vulnerable app loads serialized Java objects from a jar:file: URI, it may load attacker-controlled code and execute it. or access to jar archive file*\n", "hints_text": "You are using a bad uri.\n\nThis is how it should look like: `jar:file://path/to/myApp.jar\\!/com/example/data.txt` (e.g. `file://`\n\nThis is catched by rule 931130 at PL2.\n> This is how it should look like: `jar:file://path/to/myApp.jar\\!/com/example/data.txt` (e.g. `file://`\n\n[RFC8089](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8089#appendix-B) shows that the `file:/path/to` (with a single `/` (slash)) is a valid syntax.\n\nI'm more curious about how can an attacker use this attack? I mean if someone uses a Java application and wants to load a jar file or similar thing (I'm not a Java expert) and he wants to use a user input...? And the user input exists (both the class and data)... How frequent is this?\n\nBtw the original request is blocked on PL4 without any modification:\n```\n920273 PL4 Invalid character in request (outside of very strict set)\n920273 PL4 Invalid character in request (outside of very strict set)\n942432 PL4 Restricted SQL Character Anomaly Detection (args): # of special characters exceeded (2)\n```\n\nOk, we should extend the rule to address this new syntax.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "You are using a bad uri.\n\nThis is how it should look like: `jar:file://path/to/myApp.jar\\!/com/example/data.txt` (e.g. `file://`\n\nThis is catched by rule 931130 at PL2.\n> This is how it should look like: `jar:file://path/to/myApp.jar\\!/com/example/data.txt` (e.g. `file://`\n\n[RFC8089](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8089#appendix-B) shows that the `file:/path/to` (with a single `/` (slash)) is a valid syntax.\n\nI'm more curious about how can an attacker use this attack? I mean if someone uses a Java application and wants to load a jar file or similar thing (I'm not a Java expert) and he wants to use a user input...? And the user input exists (both the class and data)... How frequent is this?\n\nBtw the original request is blocked on PL4 without any modification:\n```\n920273 PL4 Invalid character in request (outside of very strict set)\n920273 PL4 Invalid character in request (outside of very strict set)\n942432 PL4 Restricted SQL Character Anomaly Detection (args): # of special characters exceeded (2)\n```\n\nOk, we should extend the rule to address this new syntax.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset/commit/ded45e99bc28351370b6bf7e89e9662275792e03"], "created_at": "2025-07-09T19:14:32Z"}
{"repo": "coreruleset/coreruleset", "pull_number": 4203, "instance_id": "coreruleset__coreruleset-4203", "issue_numbers": [4194], "base_commit": "4daf81159b3b8425bfb11fad33124e31209e413c", "patch": "diff --git a/rules/REQUEST-911-METHOD-ENFORCEMENT.conf b/rules/REQUEST-911-METHOD-ENFORCEMENT.conf\nindex ec2bc4beed..7240aeb7d6 100644\n--- a/rules/REQUEST-911-METHOD-ENFORCEMENT.conf\n+++ b/rules/REQUEST-911-METHOD-ENFORCEMENT.conf\n@@ -39,7 +39,6 @@ SecRule REQUEST_METHOD \"!@within %{tx.allowed_methods}\" \\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS',\\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS/METHOD-ENFORCEMENT',\\\n     tag:'capec/1000/210/272/220/274',\\\n-    tag:'PCI/12.1',\\\n     ver:'OWASP_CRS/4.17.0-dev',\\\n     severity:'CRITICAL',\\\n     setvar:'tx.inbound_anomaly_score_pl1=+%{tx.critical_anomaly_score}'\"\ndiff --git a/rules/REQUEST-913-SCANNER-DETECTION.conf b/rules/REQUEST-913-SCANNER-DETECTION.conf\nindex b566d51d10..6cabae02db 100644\n--- a/rules/REQUEST-913-SCANNER-DETECTION.conf\n+++ b/rules/REQUEST-913-SCANNER-DETECTION.conf\n@@ -51,7 +51,6 @@ SecRule REQUEST_HEADERS:User-Agent \"@pmFromFile scanners-user-agents.data\" \\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS',\\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS/SCANNER-DETECTION',\\\n     tag:'capec/1000/118/224/541/310',\\\n-    tag:'PCI/6.5.10',\\\n     ver:'OWASP_CRS/4.17.0-dev',\\\n     severity:'CRITICAL',\\\n     setvar:'tx.inbound_anomaly_score_pl1=+%{tx.critical_anomaly_score}'\"\ndiff --git a/rules/REQUEST-920-PROTOCOL-ENFORCEMENT.conf b/rules/REQUEST-920-PROTOCOL-ENFORCEMENT.conf\nindex 3dc76df788..48c2d4a0ef 100644\n--- a/rules/REQUEST-920-PROTOCOL-ENFORCEMENT.conf\n+++ b/rules/REQUEST-920-PROTOCOL-ENFORCEMENT.conf\n@@ -519,7 +519,6 @@ SecRule &REQUEST_HEADERS:Host \"@eq 0\" \\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS',\\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS/PROTOCOL-ENFORCEMENT',\\\n     tag:'capec/1000/210/272',\\\n-    tag:'PCI/6.5.10',\\\n     ver:'OWASP_CRS/4.17.0-dev',\\\n     severity:'WARNING',\\\n     setvar:'tx.inbound_anomaly_score_pl1=+%{tx.warning_anomaly_score}',\\\n@@ -724,7 +723,6 @@ SecRule REQUEST_HEADERS:Host \"@rx (?:^([\\d.]+|\\[[\\da-f:]+\\]|[\\da-f:]+)(:[\\d]+)?$\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS',\\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS/PROTOCOL-ENFORCEMENT',\\\n     tag:'capec/1000/210/272',\\\n-    tag:'PCI/6.5.10',\\\n     ver:'OWASP_CRS/4.17.0-dev',\\\n     severity:'WARNING',\\\n     setvar:'tx.inbound_anomaly_score_pl1=+%{tx.warning_anomaly_score}'\"\n@@ -930,7 +928,6 @@ SecRule REQUEST_HEADERS:Content-Type \"!@rx ^[\\w/.+*-]+(?:\\s?;\\s*(?:action|bounda\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS',\\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS/PROTOCOL-ENFORCEMENT',\\\n     tag:'capec/1000/255/153',\\\n-    tag:'PCI/12.1',\\\n     ver:'OWASP_CRS/4.17.0-dev',\\\n     severity:'CRITICAL',\\\n     setvar:'tx.inbound_anomaly_score_pl1=+%{tx.critical_anomaly_score}'\"\n@@ -954,7 +951,6 @@ SecRule REQUEST_HEADERS:Content-Type \"@rx ^[^;\\s]+\" \\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS',\\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS/PROTOCOL-ENFORCEMENT',\\\n     tag:'capec/1000/255/153',\\\n-    tag:'PCI/12.1',\\\n     ver:'OWASP_CRS/4.17.0-dev',\\\n     severity:'CRITICAL',\\\n     setvar:'tx.content_type=|%{tx.0}|',\\\n@@ -983,7 +979,6 @@ SecRule REQUEST_HEADERS:Content-Type \"@rx charset\\s*=\\s*[\\\"']?([^;\\\"'\\s]+)\" \\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS',\\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS/PROTOCOL-ENFORCEMENT',\\\n     tag:'capec/1000/255/153',\\\n-    tag:'PCI/12.1',\\\n     ver:'OWASP_CRS/4.17.0-dev',\\\n     severity:'CRITICAL',\\\n     setvar:'tx.content_type_charset=|%{tx.1}|',\\\n@@ -1011,7 +1006,6 @@ SecRule REQUEST_HEADERS:Content-Type \"@rx charset.*?charset\" \\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS',\\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS/PROTOCOL-ENFORCEMENT',\\\n     tag:'capec/1000/255/153',\\\n-    tag:'PCI/12.1',\\\n     ver:'OWASP_CRS/4.17.0-dev',\\\n     severity:'CRITICAL',\\\n     setvar:'tx.inbound_anomaly_score_pl1=+%{tx.critical_anomaly_score}'\"\n@@ -1034,7 +1028,6 @@ SecRule REQUEST_PROTOCOL \"!@within %{tx.allowed_http_versions}\" \\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS',\\\n     tag:'OWASP_CRS/PROTOCOL-ENFORCEMENT',\\\n     tag:'capec/1000/210/272',\\\n-    tag:'PCI/6.5.10',\\\n     ver:'OWASP_